The All Progressives Congress (APC) Presidential Campaign Council has postponed the presidential campaign rally in Kano indefinitely. The rally was earlier slated for February 16, 2023. The Director Public Affairs and Spokesman of the APC Presidential Campaign Council, Festus Keyamo (SAN) confirmed to our correspondent on Friday that the rally had been postponed. In a WhatsApp message, Keyamo said,” Yes. No new date yet.” Fuel/naira crises: Protesters vandalise banks in Ogun; APC cancels rally in Ondo Appeal Court sacks Abacha, restores Wali as PDP guber candidate in Kano Asked to establish the reason behind the postponement, Keyamo replied, “general adjustment in schedule.” The rally was scheduled as part of campaign activities for the APC presidential candidate, Bola Ahmed Tinubu and his running mate, Kashim Shettima ahead of the February 25 poll.